<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IFC Launches Floating Rate Marathon Bonds Offering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the launching of a GRD 27.5
billion, which is some 94 million U.S. dollars equivalent,
domestic public offering of floating rates notes (FRN).
</P>
<P>
The five-year bond issue is IFC's third FRN transaction in the
Greek capital markets in addition to the previously issued two
fixed rate bond transactions.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue will be swapped into U.S. dollar
floating-rate funds. This transaction brings IFC's market
borrowings during the fiscal year 1998, which started on July 1,
1997, to about 915 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and also the largest
multilateral source of financing for private sector projects in
developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
