<DOCNO> XIE19970808.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Women's Volleyball Team Aims at Olympics: Lang Ping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- "In participating in this year's
World Volleyball Grand Prix, we aim at the 2000 Olympic Games in
Sydney," Lang Ping, head coach of the Chinese national women's
volleyball team, said in Macao on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The spiker-turned-coach brought her team to Macao after a fresh
reshuffle, which was the first since they won the silver medal in
last year's Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Macao is the opening stage of the five-stage preliminary rounds
of the three-day World Grand Prix series, which starts on Friday
and draws four teams including China, Russia, Italy and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Lang said at a press conference that the Grand Prix offers a
good chance for the five new recruits of her team, who average
19.8 years in age and 1.82 meters in height.
</P>
<P>
The head coach admitted that in doing so, she hopes to lift the
team's spiking power and efficiency in blocking.
</P>
<P>
Also on the team are such Olympic stars as Lai Yawen, Wu
Yongmei and Sun Yue.
</P>
<P>
"We don't have an edge over others now. We have to make every
effort trying to edge our way into the grand final," Lang said.
</P>
<P>
The American team also came out brand new, with 10 out of the
12-strong line-up being new faces. The United States finished a
poor seventh at last year's Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Team coach Mick Haley said it is really a new and young team,
but they might have a different style.
</P>
<P>
Russia, fourth at the Atlanta Olympics, showed up with almost
the same side as at the Olympics. "Our goal is to be among the
top four of this year's Grand Prix," said veteran Russian coach
Nicolai Karpol.
</P>
<P>
Italian team's coach Julio Velasco said his team needed time to
be well-coordinated in the game as they also include some new
players.
</P>
<P>
This year's World Grand Prix includes preliminary stages in
Macao, Seoul, Taipei, Hong Kong and Gifu of Japan, before the
tournament going into the grand final slated for August 29-31 in
Kobe.
</P>
<P>
The opening-day's fixtures in the Macao stage see United States
face Russia and China play Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
