<HEADLINE> Sidoti Wins Women's 10,000m Walk World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Annarita Sidoti of Italy led all the
way home to win the women's 10,000-meter walk gold medal at the 6th
World Athletics Championships here today.
</P>
<P>
Her winning time was 42 minutes 55.49 seconds, a world best this
season. World Cup silver medal winner Olimpiada Ivanova of Russia
finished second in 43:07.63 and Olga Kardopoltseva of Belarus took the
bronze in 43:30.20. It is the first gold for Italy at the current
meet.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion and world silver medallist Yelena Nikolayeva of
Russia finished a poor 10th, and World Cup winner Irina Stankina of
Russia disqualified during the race.
</P>
<P>
Sidoti, the fourth fastest walker this year behind the three
Russian entrants, set a fast pace from the start and passed the first
5,000 meters with only Ivanova and Stankina hanging tough in her wake.
</P>
<P>
With 11 laps to go, the small Italian leader changed to a higher
gear to drop Ivanova 10 meters behind. The following four laps saw
Stankina, the world leader this year, walk closely at Sidoti's heels,
waiting chance to overtake her.
</P>
<P>
But Stankina got three warnings in a row within the next 400 meters
and had to quit the battle.
</P>
<P>
Sidoti met no challenge in the remaining distance, heading home for
a surprised victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
