<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Romania to Expand Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Romania have
agreed to make joint efforts to expand trade and investment
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
At the 14th session of the Pakistan-Romanian Joint Commission
for Economic Cooperation held here on Wednesday and today, the two
countries agreed to make efforts to promote bilateral trade on a
balanced and mutually-beneficial basis, official sources said
today.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed the Convention on Avoidance of
Double Taxation and Prevention of Fiscal Evasion With Respect to
Taxes on Income and Capital which was initialed on July 31 this
year in Islamabad, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The convention would soon be made effective after ratification
formalities are completed, they said, adding that it will pave the
groundwork for expanding investment and joint ventures between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
There is a tremendous scope for Romanian investment in
Pakistan, particularly in the field of infrastructure development,
said Javed Burki, secretary of the joint commission's economic
affairs division, who led the Pakistani delegation at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Industry and Commerce Ministry Secretary Nicolae
Staiculescu, who led a 10-member Romanian delegation, assured that
his country's investors would continue their investment in
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, Pakistan and Romania also reviewed
the implementation of the decisions of the 13th session of the
joint commission which was held in April, 1995 in Bucharest.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that the 15th session of the joint
commission would be held in Bucharest at a date to be decided
through diplomatic channels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
