<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Perec Pulls out of Women's 200m </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Marie-Jose Perec of France pulled out
of the women's 200 meters semifinals at the 6th World Athletics
Championships here today.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic champion didn't make a start in the first group for
unknown reasons. Perec, who took both the 200m and 400m golds at
Atlanta Games last year, and announced that she wouldn't take part in
the current meet due to poor condition, changed her mind later just
shortly before the meet. She had competed in the first and second
rounds in a good form.
</P>
<P>
With the absence of Perec, Merlene Ottey of Jamaica, defending
champion in the 200 meters, has a very good chance to retain the world
title.
</P>
<P>
In the second group minutes earlier, the 37-year-old Ottey romped
home in style to clock the fastest time of the day in 22.26 seconds,
the world second best this year.
</P>
<P>
Ottey, who finished a disappointed 7th in the 100 meters on August
3, eased her speed obviously in the final 50 meters today, but the
time is much faster than the 22.47 clocking, her best this year before
the race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
