<HEADLINE> Mozambican FM Ends Visit to Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Foreign Minister
Leonardo Simao today ended his four-day visit to Angola which was
aimed at strengthening cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Angola, the Mozambican minister had wide
contacts with Angolan leaders and discussed with them on how to
expand bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In a news briefing before leaving for home today, Simao said
the two sides agreed that bilateral cooperation should be
expanded into every field after peace is realized in the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that the governments of Angola and
Mozambique will review cooperation agreements signed by the two
countries in the near future.
</P>
<P>
In view of new situations in both countries, the two
governments will take steps to expand bilateral cooperation,
especially cooperation between private businesses, he added.
</P>
<P>
Simao also expressed his optimism over the Angolan peace
process, saying that the day when final peace comes true in
Angola is not far off although the opposition UNITA had delayed
in fully implementing the Lusaka peace accord.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican foreign minister arrived here Monday for
visit to Angola. 
</P>
