<HEADLINE> Faumuina Wins Women's Discus World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Beatrice Faumuina of New Zealand won
the women's discus gold medal at the 6th World Athletics Championships
here today.
</P>
<P>
Her winning distance was 66.82 meters ahead of Ellina Zvereva of
Belarus's 65.90m and Natalya Sadova of Russia's 65.14m. It is the
first gold medal for New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Faumina, 1997 world leader with a personal best of 68.52 meters,
fouled her first two tosses, but her heave in the third round was good
enough to settle the gold.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Zvereva threw her longest in the second round,
but posed no threat to the winner.
</P>
<P>
"It was almost like what I had done in the qualifying. I can
honestly tell you I didn't want to start out like that, but it was
good to come back in the third," Faumuina said at the press
conference.
</P>
<P>
Zvereva told the press:"Throughout the whole final I was waiting a
good 67-meter-throw, but I didn't put together a good one." 
</P>
</TEXT>
