<HEADLINE> Kumbernuss Wins Women's Shot Put Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Astrid Kumbernuss of Germany retained
her title in the women's discus final at the 6th World Athletics
Championships here today.
</P>
<P>
Her winning toss was 20.71 meters, the third best this year in the
world. Vita Pavlysh of Ukraine chased Kumbernuss hard, but she
finished five centimeters short of the winner. Stephanie Storp of
Germany landed the bronze at 19.22. China's Huang Zhihong, world
champion in 1991 and 1993, was beaten into the fourth place.
</P>
<P>
Kumbernuss, defending champion and Olympic gold medal winner, led
the opening round with a mighty 20.59 meters, and landed her winner in
the next try.
</P>
<P>
Pavlysh, Olympic silver medallist and world indoor champion this
year, got a 20.57 heave in the same round. The 28-year-old went all
out in the final round, but her 20.66 toss was not strong enough to
bring her the gold.
</P>
<P>
"I wanted to show who is the boss in the ring. I knew it would be
difficult and I couldn't get into the competition relaxed, always
thinking too much," revealed Kumbernuss at the press conference.
</P>
<P>
A disappointed Pavlysh exclaimed:"The final was hard as they always
are. Here the difference between me and the first was five
centimeters, but I am sure that I will break these bloody centimeters
to my favour eventually!" 
</P>
