<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Resume Power Export to S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Work to rebuild the eastern
power line from Mozambique's giant Cahora Bassa Dam to South
Africa has been completed, a local media report said.
</P>
<P>
The job was completed on Tuesday and experts are now carrying
out inspections along the line before switching on power for
trial transmission.
</P>
<P>
The line will supply power to South Africa from the dam in
Mozambique's north-western province of Tete.
</P>
<P>
Officials said work on the second line between Cahora Bassa
and South Africa will be completed by the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
The entire job consisted of putting 2,200 pylons into position
along a 900-kilometer transmission line within Mozambican
territory.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 pylons were destroyed during 17 years of civil
war in Mozambique. 
</P>
