<HEADLINE> Cargo Plane Crash May Kill 4 People Aboard in Miami </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The four people on board a
DC-8 cargo jet that crashed near Miami International Airport today
were presumed dead and four others on the ground were confirmed
injured.
</P>
<P>
The plane, belonging to Fine Airlines Inc. and was carrying
cargo to Santo Domingo in the Dominican Republic, crashed just off
a runway on takeoff at the airport at 12:35 p.m. EDT. Airline
officials said four persons were on the plane -- three crew
members and a security person. They were presumed dead.
</P>
<P>
It crashed near an intersection and officials said it hit at
least one building. A number of cars were seen in the wreckage.
Local TV reports said four people on the ground were injured in
the crash.
</P>
<P>
The plane first hit at the edge of an empty lot. It then
skidded across the lot, breaking up into flaming wreckage that
slammed across a busy street and slid into the front of a row of
small businesses and stores. It wasn't immediately clear how badly
the buildings were damaged.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was unclear. The weather was clear. The
National Transportation Safety Board has sent a team of
investigators to the site.
</P>
<P>
It was the second big cargo plane crash in the United States in
eight days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
