<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia to Privatize Power Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will soon privatize the
Zambia Electricity Supply Corporation (ZESCO) to attract private
capital to the development of the power sector, a government
minister announced today.
</P>
<P>
Suresh Desai, minister of energy and water development, said
the on-going privatization process in the country will result in
significant economic expansion and improvement.
</P>
<P>
In view of this prospect, the government has recognized the
need for a vibrant and healthy electric utility system to drive
the economy, Desai said when he opened a two-day workshop on
hydro-power and transmission line policy near Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
The minister urged all participants from Europe, the Americas,
Asia and the sub-Saharan Africa, to discuss the issue frankly and
constructively to help the government draw up an energy policy.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, a World Bank representative said that energy sector
is not only a source of power vital to the development of the
country, but one of revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
