<HEADLINE> Neolithic Ovens, Pottery Found in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Archaeologists of Greece and
Bulgaria have found parts of walls with wooden frames, ovens,
pottery and benches dating back to 5,000 BC. in the ruins of a
neolithic settlement near Promachonas, Serres in northern Greece.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) today quoted the
director of the Kavala department of classical and prehistoric
antiquities as saying that the find was particularly significant
since it revealed a great deal about the cultural relations which
developed between the Aegean and the Balkan region. 
</P>
