<HEADLINE> Fangcheng Port Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The construction of two
10,000-ton shipping berths started today at Fangcheng Port,
southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The container and bulk cargo berths will include wharfs,
warehouses, railway spurs, highways, and power, water and
telecommunications facilities.
</P>
<P>
The berths, which will be constructed at a cost of 663.8
million yuan, will be completed in three years and will have a
total annual handling capacity of 2.64 million tons. The Asian
Development Bank will extend a 32 million US dollar loan to
finance the construction of the berths.
</P>
<P>
Ten of Fangcheng's existing berths are rated at 10,000
tons. Fangcheng Port currently has links with ports in 64
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Completion on the two berths will provide Fangcheng with a
total annual handling capacity of 11 million tons, up from 3.04
million tons handled in the first half of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
