<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia's "Unbeatable" New Missiles Available Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Russia is to start selling its
newly-designed "Yakhont" missiles on the world weapons market
soon, the Itar-Tass news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The missile, which destroys aircraft carriers, frigates and
surfaced submarines, has a range of up to 300 kilometers and is
equipped with an advanced radar homing system designed by "Granit"
research institute.
</P>
<P>
Russian navy experts believed that the missile is impervious to
attack.
</P>
<P>
It can be launched from submarines, from surface ships and by
coast guard launchers on the ground. Travelling at twice the speed
of sound and at very low attitude, "Yakhont" remains undetectable
until it explodes, they said.
</P>
<P>
Russian military experts say initial interest indicates sales
will exceed their expectations. Some Asia-Pacific countries and
Middle East countries have already shown interest in the new
missile, they said.
</P>
<P>
Itar-Tass said the Russian missile is far superior in
every way to the much advertised U.S. Tomahawk missile and its
French and British counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Russian designers and navy specialists believe "Yakhont" will
have no competition in the world armaments market for at least a
quarter of a century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
