<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) today
urged Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat to step up the
investigation into the suicide bombing which killed 15 people and
injured 150 in a Jewish market in Jerusalem on July 30.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Arafat sent on behalf of the 15 EU nations,
Luxembourg's Foreign Minister Jacques Poos said the Palestinian
authorities would not only show their good faith but would also
contribute to faster progress in the enquiry and finding out who
was responsible for the attack.
</P>
<P>
The EU considered it "absolutely necessary" for the Palestinian
authorities to cooperate fully with the Israelis on security
matters and in the ongoing enquiry, Poos said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister of Luxembourg, which currently holds the
six-month rotating EU presidency, added that the EU was satisfied
with Arafat's condemnation of the terrorist act.
</P>
<P>
Hamas extremists have claimed responsibility for the bombing
which they described in a leaflet as "a practical response to the
Zionist practices against" the Palestinians. 
