ignited in the crowd, seats thrown and bottles hurled onto the
court following Yugoslavia's win.
</P>
<P>
Police outside Melbourne Park fought to bring the crowd under
control as supporters of the two teams went on a rampage.
</P>
<P>
Australia held a 38-34 edge at halftime and accelerated away
with a 13-0 run from the opening of the second half.
</P>
<P>
In the other quarter-finals, Argentina beat Lithuania 74-57 and
Puerto Rico edged out Spain 77-71. 
