<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, August 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO -- The Bosnian Presidency Friday reached agreement on
the allocation of ambassadorships among the country's three ethnic
groups. But they failed to agree on other provisions of joint
statehood, such as passports, citizenship and opening airports,
together with currency and flag.
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein Friday called upon
Iran to pursue a policy of cooperation, stabilization of relations
and development of bilateral ties on the genuine and clear basis.
Saddam issued the call in his address on the occasion of the lapse
of nine years after the end of the Iraqi-Iranian war, according to
the Iraqi News Agency.
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Countries in central and eastern Europe including
some of the former Soviet republics will soon be funded by the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) in their research and
development.
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Malaysia and the Philippines Friday agreed to
take an immediate action to address the problems of illegal
activities in the Sulu Sea and upgrading communication
facilities. The agreement was reached at the five-day fourth
Malaysia-Philippines Border Patrol Coordinating Group (BPCG)
Meeting which ended here Friday.
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi has stressed his
country's continuous commitment to peacekeeping mission in south
Lebanon despite the disastrous helicopter crash Wednesday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
