<HEADLINE> Malaysian PM Stresses Togetherness on ASEAN Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad today called upon all member countries of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) to continue to
nurture and nourish the spirit of ASEAN togetherness.
</P>
<P>
"In all our undertakings and ventures, the spirit of ASEAN
togetherness prevailed and has been our guiding principle," he
said in his message on the occasion of the 30th anniversary of
ASEAN aired by Radio and Television Malaysia (RTM) tonight.
</P>
<P>
He said much have been achieved due to the spirit of ASEAN --
doing things the ASEAN way which means practicing consultation and
seeking consensus by exercising self-restraint and maintaining
mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
"There have been times when our very existence and cohesiveness
had been put to the test, but we have always survived and come out
stronger," Mahathir said.
</P>
<P>
He added that ASEAN shall continue to nurture and nourish this
principle to ensure greater prosperity and strength.
</P>
<P>
"We are fully committed to the goals and ideals of ASEAN and we
are confident that ASEAN will achieve greater progress in the
future," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian leader was also of the view that ASEAN youths
should be guided in the best possible way so that they could
contribute to the future of the region.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Let us guide them in the ASEAN way with the ASEAN
spirit so that they will become good, responsible and worthy
citizens of ASEAN."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said that as the world is more complex and demanding
ASEAN leaders should reflect on some of the past problems and
difficulties so that repetition would not occur.
</P>
<P>
"As we stand on the threshold of the 21st Century we must be
fully equipped to manage the challenges that will come with the
new millennium," he said, adding "with the right attitude,
knowledge and commitment, and drawing from ASEAN's past lessons we
will be able to surmount the challenges that may emerge."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said Malaysia is proud to be a member of ASEAN and to
have contributed something towards the success of the association.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Malaysia, Indonesia, the Philippines,
Singapore, Thailand, Brunei, Vietnam, Laos and Myanmar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
