<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Hit Southern Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rain hit Russia's
southern Krasnodar region and the Karachayevo-Cherkess Republic on
August 4-6, causing damage of about 70 billion roubles (some 11
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Flooding caused by the rains from August 4 to 6 destroyed or
damaged 1,470 houses in the Krasnoarmeisky and Slavyansky
districts in Krasnodar, causing an estimated loss of 67 billion
roubles, Itar-Tass quoted the Russian
Emergencies Ministry as saying today.
</P>
<P>
A six-hour downpour during the evening of August 6 in the
Karachayevo-Cherkess Republic, caused damage worth an estimated
380 million roubles (63,000 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Itar-Tass didn't report any casualties in the affected
areas where emergency repair work is now under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
