<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grobbelaar Cleared at Match-fix Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Former Liverpool goalkeeper Bruce
Grobbelaar was cleared of corruptly accepting money to try and
influence football matches at Winchester Crown Court on Friday.
</P>
<P>
After a week of deliberations, the jury told judge Justice
McCulloch that they were unable to reach a decision on a final
count against Zimbabwean Grobbelaar.
</P>
<P>
The prosecution offered no further evidence against Grobbelaar
and the judge immediately ordered a verdict of not guilty to be
entered.
</P>
<P>
After the decision was announced, Grobbelaar's wife Debbie left
the public gallery in tears and was ushered into a conference room
in the court building, where she was reunited with her husband.
</P>
<P>
The order brought to an end the 10-week retrial in which all
four defendants were cleared of allegations of conspiring to
"throw" the results of English Premiership matches for the benefit
of a Far East betting syndicate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
