<HEADLINE> CNCP, Husky Sign Enhance Oil Recovery Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The China National Petroleum
Corp. (CNPC) today signed with Canadian Husky Oil Co. China's
first EOR (enhance oil recovery) contract for the Pucheng Oilfield
in Henan province.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, Husky Oil Co. will be the sole operator and
investor for the project. Husky is expected to undertake the
contracted workload during the assessment period. The contract
also stipulates terms on sharing profits after the oilfield goes
into commercial operation.
</P>
<P>
Pucheng, part of CNPC's Zhongyuan Oilfield, is a 17-year-old
oil gusher. Existing development technology such as water
injection has proved ineffective. 
</P>
</TEXT>
