<HEADLINE> Tracklaying of Jinhua-Wenzhou Railway Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Tracklaying of the
Jinhua-Wenzhou Railway, the first railway project jointly funded
by Hong Kong and Zhejiang Province, was completed today.
</P>
<P>
The 251-kilometer railway runs through 10 counties and cities
with a combined population of 14.5 million. One fifth of the
railway line are tunnels.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of local officials and people from all walks of life
attended a ceremony marking the completion of the project which is
expected to promote development in resource-rich but
poverty-stricken areas in the coastal province.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Railways has also invested in the
three-billion-yuan project which local experts point to as a
highly successful experiment designed to encourage state and local
governments to cooperate in infrastructure construction
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
