<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Cape Town's 2004 Olympic bid
received a huge shot in the arm on Thursday when the African
Amateur Athletics Confederation (AAAC) unanimously endorsed a
supporting decision.
</P>
<P>
AAAC President Lamine Diack announced the decision in Athens,
according to media reports.
</P>
<P>
