<HEADLINE> Chinese Money Market Reports Thin Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Turnover on the Shanghai-based
interbank money market plunged by more than 40 percent over the
previous month to 5.831 billion yuan in July, down 63.53 percent
over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown shows that borrowings totaled 2.904 billion yuan
during the period and the lendings 2.921 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Outstanding borrowings and lendings added up to 3.667 billion
yuan, a dive of 69.3 percent over the previous month and nearly 80
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that a major factor behind the thin fund trading
last month was that money demand outside Shanghai shrank
drastically while the deposits of the financial institutions in
the municipality remained sufficient.
</P>
<P>
The interbank rate maintained the level of June owing to a dull
trading on the money market. Nevertheless, the seven-day
transaction volume at the Shanghai interbank money market
continued to top the list of all the trading items last month,
accounting for 64.09 percent of the total national turnover.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
