<DOCNO> XIE19970808.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Output Value Up 8.4 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Sustained summer heat and less
working days slowed down the growth speed of China's industrial
production in July.
</P>
<P>
The country last month posted a year-on-year industrial output
value growth of 8.4 percent, dropping 1.4 percentage points than
the figure in the first half year, according to a monthly report
on China's industrial production released here today by the State
Statistical Bureau (SSB).
</P>
<P>
The report indicated that the country's industry at or above
the township-level posted added values totaling 162.5 billion
yuan, of which state-owned sector and enterprises controlled by
the state posted 93.1 billion yuan, or a rise of 5.8 percent than
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The added values generated by state enterprises increased 3.9
percent; the amount by the collective enterprises, up 7.7 percent;
and the values registered by other economic sectors, up 11.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Of China's 30 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities
(excluding Tibet), only Liaoning, Anhui, Guangdong and Qinghai
witnessed faster growth than the previous year, while the rest
registered slower growth.
</P>
<P>
Added values in light industry stood at 66.3 billion yuan, up
8.3 percent, while the added values in heavy industry registered
96.2 billion yuan, registering an increase of 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Energy output also saw slower growth. In July, China produced
energy equivalent to 103 million tons of standard coal, a decrease
of 1.6 percent than the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The coal production in the month stood at 109 million tons,
down 2.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of crude oil in July reached 13.79 million tons, up
1.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Owing to the hot weather and the rise of electricity
consumption, China generated 96.4 billion kwh of electricity in
July.
</P>
<P>
Raw material output saw smooth increase last month. Growth
rates of iron, steel, steel products, ten non-ferrous metals, and
ten major chemical materials, including sulphuric acid, nitric
acid, soda ash, ethylene and chemical fibers, ranged from 10.3
percent to 21.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The sales to production ratio in the month hit 96.34 percent, a
year-on-year rise of 0.51 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the industrial profits kept upward
trend. The composite index for industrial returns stood at 88.04
percent, up 4.24 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
Chinese enterprises in the month had 63.4 billion yuan in
profits, up 34.5 percent; of which state enterprises earned 12.1
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Experts with SSB said that China's industrial economy has
geared up to the better turn, even though still in "the initial
and recovering period". One expert noted that the overall economic
returns are still in low level. "Efforts have still to be made on
deepening reform and optimizing the industrial mix in the future,"
he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
