in 1996, up 30 percent from that in the previous year. It is
estimated that by 2000, that number will exceed 70,000.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Australian consulate in Shanghai said that
they will make things easy for Chinese tourists on entry and exit
visas. China is Australia's fifth largest trading partner, and is
expected to rise to the third by 2000. 
</P>
