<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Newspaper Marks ASEAN Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) is playing an important role in regional and
international affairs, Vietnam's leading newspaper Nhan Dan said
in a commentary today marking the 30th anniversary of the
organization.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN has made important achievements in many fields over the
past three decades and become "one of the most successful regional
organizations in the world," said the commentary.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN, which was founded in 1967 and now comprises nine
countries, produces 90 percent of the world's rubber, 70 percent
of all tin and vegetable oil, and 60 percent of timber. The annual
output of the member countries totals more than 630 billion U.S.
dollars, it said.
</P>
<P>
The organization's trade volume has rapidly increased in the
past 10 years with an annual foreign investment of 13.5 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's admission to the group in 1995 marked a step of
development in its relations with other ASEAN members, and dozens
of economic and commercial agreements have been effectively
implemented between them, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
