<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Volume in May Up with Prices Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's
re-exports and imports increased by 2.2 and 5.3 percent,
respectively, in May over a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, that of domestic exports decreased by 1.8 percent,
according to the statistics released by the Census and Statistics
Department today.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the January-May period this year with the same period
 of last year, the volume of Hong Kong's re-exports decreased by
5.3 percent and that of domestic exports decreased by 3.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing May 1997 with May 1996, the prices of re-exports and
domestic exports decreased by 1.7 percent and 2.1 percent
respectively. Import prices also fell by 2.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
As regards price changes in the January-May period this year
over the same period last year, the prices of re-exports and
domestic exports decreased by 1.4 and 2.0 percent respectively,
while import prices decreased by 2.5 percent.  
</P>
