<HEADLINE> Guangxi Has First Automated Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The first "self-help" bank that
provides 24-hour services in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region is now in operation in the region's capital
Nanning.
</P>
<P>
Local branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
(ICBC), one of the four major commercial banks in China, is the
operator of the bank. The automated branch bought equipment from
the IBM of the United States and the German Siemens.
</P>
<P>
Banking specialists say that this is a move taken by ICBC to
edge its competitiveness in the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Holders of the Peony Credit Card issued by ICBC can use their
cards as a key to get into the bank at any time, where automatic
teller machines, multi-media computer systems for service
consulting and other banking equipments are available.
</P>
<P>
Customers can use all service facilities with no need to pay
any charge, except the automatic strong-boxes, according to ICBC
officials.  
