<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stock Market Bullish in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The monthly turnover value on
the Hong Kong Stock Exchange in July continued at a high level
after the heavy trading atmosphere in June.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover for July was 409.60 billion HK dollars (52.85
billion U.S. dollars), compared with 398.97 billion HK dollars
(51.48 billion U.S. dollars) in June.
</P>
<P>
But average daily turnover for the 21 trading days in July was
19.50 billion HK dollars (2.52 billion U.S. dollars), a decrease
of 7 percent from the previous month.
</P>
<P>
A total of 224.64 million shares changed hands in July,
up from 184.58 billion HK dollars in June. The average daily
turnover by volume in July was 10.69 billion shares,up 10 percent
from June.
</P>
<P>
The total number of trades in July was 3,745,843, which was 16
percent more than that in June.
</P>
<P>
Average daily turnover for the first seven months of this year
was 13.64 billion HK dollars (1.76 billion U.S. dollars), compared
with 4.85 billion HK dollars (625 million U.S. dollars) in the
corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover by value was 1,949.89 billion HK dollars (251.60
billion U.S. dollars) during the first seven months of this year,
compared with 699 billion HK dollars in the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
During the first seven months of this year, the average daily
turnover by volume was 6.95 billion shares, compared with 1.79
billion shares in the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 993.31 billion shares were traded during the first
seven months of this year, up from 257.80 million shares in the
corresponding period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index at the end of July was 16,365.71, an
increase of 8 percent from last month and 53 percent from July
1996.
</P>
<P>
The market capitalization on July 31 was 4,607.19 billion HK
dollars (594.48 billion U.S. dollars), an increase of 73 percent
on the same date of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
