<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Further on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline further on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index fell by another 9.32 points to close at
1,943.92 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 171.47 million units, worth
782.99 million Singapore dollars (about 536.29 million U.S.
dollars). Declines led advances by 161 to 156 while 293 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 11.21 million units. It was followed by
Asia Food &AMP; Properties which had 8.3 million shares traded. The
United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign was next with 6.98 million
shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
UniCor led the gainers of the day as it rose by 57 cents to
finish at two Singapore dollars. Local food and soft drinks maker
F&AMP;N increased by 30 cents to end at 10.2 Singapore dollars while
the Thai Prime Fund was 25 cents higher at 8.7 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign was
the most actively traded stock as it declined by 80 cents to end
at 26.4 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank of Singapore (DBS)
Foreign and the UOB Foreign fell by 70 cents each to close at 17.4
and 13.7 Singapore dollars respectively. The Singapore Technology
Auto Foreign was 44 cents lower at 3.26 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
