<HEADLINE> Open Water Swimming Postponed due to Typhoon Tina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Organizers of the Pan Pacific
swimming championships said Friday that the 25-kilometer open
water event would be postponed because of a strong approaching
typhoon.
</P>
<P>
Typhoon Tina is currently southwest of Okinawa and is moving
northwest at a speed of 18 kilometers per hour and is expected to
be closest to Fukuoka early Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The organizers said they decided to postpone the men's and
women's 25km races by one day until Sunday, at a special course in
waters off Ohara Beach in Fukuoka. 
