<HEADLINE> Overseas Tourists In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's tourism management
commission reports that by June of this year China's largest city
had 782,700 tourists, 16.5 percent higher than that for the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
A municipal government official says that tourism is a major
part of the city's service industry and earned 1.17 billion US
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai established its tourism management commission to
accelerate tourism development by co-operating with countries with
developed tourism industries like Australia, Japan and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has also made its booming tourism known to the world
through the Internet. As China's economic center, Shanghai has
concentrated on developing urban tourism which combines scenery
with culture and commerce.
</P>
<P>
By working with other cities, Shanghai has developed the
"Essential Travel in China," which attracted more overseas
tourists. 
</P>
