<HEADLINE> Argentina Crushes Lithuania in U23 Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Argentina lived up to its top
billing in Group A when it crushed Lithuania by 17 points in a
quarter-final match of the Men's Under 23 World Championships in
Melbourne on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Argentina, which headed the Group A table with a 4-1 ledger,
jumped Lithuania to lead 29-9 midway through the first half to win
74-57.
</P>
