<HEADLINE> Northeast China City Moves to Help Urban Poor Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang city, capital of
Liaoning province, has provided assistance to over 230,000 local
employees, including 130,000 workers from state firms, through the
city government's program to help poor urban families.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang, with over 10,000 enterprises and more than two
million factory workers, is a major heavy industrial base in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Two years ago, the city government set up a special fund with
contributions coming from the government revenue, social security
funds and donations from profit-making companies and individuals.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, the fund, dubbed as the "Warm Program", has
collected nearly 50 million yuan and will be used to help
"extremely poor workers" in the city, who are numbered at nearly
40,000 at present.
</P>
<P>
Poor families will receive help from the fund when they need
financial assistance. Officials in charge often visit poor
families and distribute relife money.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city government has issued a series of policies
to help these families. So far, over 10,000 poor families have
been covered by the official poverty-relief network which has kept
a file of all the poor families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
