<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberian President Defines Role of ECOMOG </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 8 (Xinhua) -- President Charles Taylor of
Liberia has signed into law his first bill which clarified the
role of the west African peacekeeping force operating in his
country.
</P>
<P>
By the enactment, which was in effect from last Tuesday, the
peacekeeping force, known as ECOMOG, has been limited to the
maintenance of security while the police and the judiciary handle
civil and criminal matters.
</P>
<P>
The legislation also empowers Taylor to contact the Economic
Community of West African States (ECOWAS) on further ECOMOG
assignment, according to a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG was sent by ECOWAS to Liberia in 1990 at the heat of
the country's civil war, which was ignited by the then factional
leader Taylor.
</P>
<P>
Its efforts have brought to the successful disarmament and
demobilization of the warring factions, and finally ensured the
July 19 elections that put Taylor to the nation's top seat.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed in Abuja, Nigeria, by the
factional leaders a year ago, ECOMOG will help restructure the
Liberian army and police force in six months after the new
government is in place on August 2.
</P>
<P>
The stay of ECOMOG, however, may be extended because the
training of the forces has not begun.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970808.0168 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China Power Plant Insured for Over 10 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Ertan Power Station in
southwest China's Sichuan province has been insured for 11.9
billion yuan against any possible risks.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Ertan Hydropower Development
Co. Ltd. disclosed that they have insured the electro-mechanical
equipment, the diversion canal and underground workshops for the
power project against possible accidents at the Property Company
of the People's Insurance Corporation of China (PICC) and two
foreign insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
Built at the lower reaches of the Yalong river in Sichuan
province in cooperation with foreign companies, the Ertan
Hydropower Station, the second largest hydropower station in
China, will have a total generating capacity of 3.3 million kw.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 21 billion yuan, construction of the
project started on Sept. 14 of 1991 and is scheduled to be
completed in 2000 with an annual power generating capacity of 17
billion kwh at first.
</P>
<P>
According to schedule, the first generating unit of the power
plant will go into trial operation in June 1998 and commercial
operation in October of the same year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
