<HEADLINE> 20 Rebels killed, 30 Injured In North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 Tamil rebels were
killed and over 30 others injured Thursday in a confrontation with
the government troops in Northern Province of the country, a
military spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the rebels offered a resistance with medium
guns and small arms to advancing troops east of Paliyankulam. The
troops with support of armor and artillery forced the rebels to
withdraw with heavy casualties.
</P>
<P>
The troops estimated they killed at least 20 rebels and
wounded more than 30 others while five soldiers were killed and 28
others injured during the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The troops continue to dominate areas ahead of defenses, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, referring to another incident happened in north
Mannar, the spokesman said two soldiers and five rebels were
killed and 7 other rebels wounded during the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting for a separate state in the
north and east of the country since 1983. 
</P>
