<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Artificial Rain Eases Water Shortage in Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xinin, August 8 (Xinhua) -- China induced 200 million cubic
meters of artificial rainfall over Qinghai province during the
past three months as a way to increase water flow in the Yellow
River.
</P>
<P>
The river, the second largest in China that provides irrigation
for seven provinces in north and northwest China, has been plagued
by frequent drought these last six to seven years.
</P>
<P>
The reduced water volume causes flowcuts in the lower reaches
of the river each year, which bring about heavy losses to
industrial and agricultural production alone the river banks.
</P>
<P>
Beginning late last April, the Qinghai Meteorological
Department started to make artificial rain in the region which is
in the upper reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
According to hydrological officials, the operation will
continue till the end of September, and the goal is to add another
280 million cubic meters of water to the Yellow River flow.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
