<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Issues Public Bonds in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank said
here today that it has launched public bonds worth 300 million
U.S. dollars in the United States domestic bond market on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The bonds, with a coupon rate of 6.22 percent per annum payable
semiannually and a 30-year maturity, were priced at 100 percent,
the bank said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The bonds will be unlisted and have put options every five
years starting from the 10th year. Settlement and clearing of the
bonds will be through the U.S. Federal Reserve bookentry system.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds will be part of the ADB's ordinary capital
resources used in its ordinary lending operations.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1966 to promote economic growth in the Asian
Pacific region, the Manila-based bank has 56 members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
