<HEADLINE> Milk Output Up in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's milk output had
increased from 365 million liters in 1992 to 600 million liters
last year, a local daily, The Monitor, reported today.
</P>
<P>
Kezimbira Miyingo, Minister of State for Agriculture in charge
of animal husbandry was quoted as saying that Uganda's dairy
industry is based on indigenous animals which produce about 97
percent of all the milk.
</P>
<P>
Miyingo made the remark while he accompanied the visiting
Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa to inspect a dairy farm in
Busunju, over 30 miles northwest of Kampala Thursday.
</P>
<P>
James Mulwana, owner of the farm said his farm which has 480
heads of cattle with machinery to process over 12,000 liters of
milk per day exports cattle to Rwanda and also plans to start a
dairy farm in Tanzania.  
</P>
</TEXT>
