<HEADLINE> WB to Grant Turkey One Billion Dollars Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank (WB) is to grant a
one-billion-U.S. dollar loan to support Turkey's eight-year
compulsory education reform.
</P>
<P>
The money is part of a total of 1.5-billion-dollar WB aid
for Turkey's health, education as well as infrastructure,
according to semi-official Anatolia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted WB officials, whose names were not given,
as saying that the sum would be extended to Turkey within
the framework of the Country Aid Strategy Program.
</P>
<P>
The eight-year compulsory reform bill, proposed by Turkish
Education Ministry, are now under a white hot debate in the
Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The controversial bill have triggered strong opposition from
the pro-Islamic Welfare Party led by former prime minister
Necmettin Erbakan since its adoption because it will possibly
lead to the closure of religious schools.
</P>
<P>
The Welfare Party vowed that they would use all means to
block the approval of the education bill. 
</P>
