<HEADLINE> Xiamen Prepares for Property Rights Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The '97 China Enterprise Merger
and Investment Fair will be held in Xiamen, a port city in China's
Fujian Province early this September.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which is sponsored by the State Commission for
Restructuring the Economic System, the Industrial Development
Organization of the United Nations, and the Xiamen city
government, will provide a place for overseas investors to get
involved in state-owned enterprises and negotiating property
rights. And Chinese textile and cement producers who want to
invest in other developing countries will have an opportunity to
look for partners.
</P>
<P>
"The fair will provide a chance for China's large enterprises
to talk about merging smaller ones as well," local officials say.
</P>
<P>
China is expected to have more than 1,000 mergers this year,
since it has become a popular way for the state sector to get rid
of its heavy losses. But this has also triggered a sharp increase
in the number of unemployed workers who used to believe in "cradle
to grave" welfare benefits.
</P>
<P>
There will be many investment possibilities announced at the
event, in the food, drink, chemical, electronics, auto-parts,
energy, transportation, telecommunications and environmental
protection industries.
</P>
<P>
The organization committee says that they have received various
feedback from both Chinese and overseas enterprises, saying most
of them will attend the event. 
</P>
