<HEADLINE> Israel Arrests 200 Palestinians in 10 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Israeli security forces
arrested 12 Palestinians in the West Bank Thursday night,
bringing the number of Palestinians picked up since the suicide
bombing attack on July 30 to over 200.
</P>
<P>
In the 10-day sweeping campaign to crack down on the
infrastructure of Hamas and other radical Palestinian
organizations in the areas still under Israeli occupation,
Israeli soldiers and undercover units raided mosques and other
institutions affiliated with Hamas and confiscated what Israel
believed inflammatory materials, according to a report of the
state-run Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
The Israel Defense Forces (IDF) even arrested those so-called
hostile Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Fearing an outbreak of violence at the end of today's
prayers in the mosques, security forces have beefed up their
positions in the West Bank including East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there has been no breakthrough in identifying the
two suicide bombers who killed 13 Israelis and wounded 168 in
their bombing attack at the Mahaneh Yehuda Market in Jerusalem
on July 30. Some reports said that they came from Ein Hilwe refugee
camp in Lebanon, while others claimed they were from the West
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli authorities originally concluded that the two men
were just the two Hamas activists in a village near Hebron,
who were missing more than a year ago. But blood-tests of
the families proved wrong. 
</P>
