<HEADLINE> Philippines Marks ASEAN's 30th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines today marked the
30th founding anniversary of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) by launching a series of programs.
</P>
<P>
Today's celebration highlights included the formal inauguration
of the ASEAN Village, a garden with miniature structures
representing each ASEAN member country at the old city of
Intramuros in Manila.
</P>
<P>
A portion of the garden was devoted to the five signatories of
the 1967 Bangkok Declaration which launched the ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Another highlight of the observance is the staging of the
"ASEAN Battle of the Brains," a television quiz show in Manila
with student participants from all ASEAN member states.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines actually kicked off its celebration on Thursday
night when President Fidel Ramos witnessed the presentation of
four stamps to commemorate the 30th anniversary of the ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Also to be inaugurated on August 13 is the ASEAN Promenade at
the Cultural Center of the Philippines in which the national flags
of all ASEAN member countries would be on display.
</P>
<P>
Other activities in Manila include a week-long show of ASEAN
films, an ASEAN lecture series and the inauguration of the ASEAN
Regional Center for Biodiversity at the University of the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups nine of the 10 countries comprising the
Southeast Asian region, including Brunei, Indonesia, Laos,
Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and
Vietnam.  
</P>
</TEXT>
