<HEADLINE> Nigerian Airline to Resume Nairobi Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria Airways is to resume
flights to Kenya after a five-year break due to cash disputes,
the Daily Nation newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
A bilateral air services agreement was reached this week by
representatives of the two governments, said the report.
</P>
<P>
However, Nigeria will pay about 16,000 U.S. Dollars owed by
Nigeria Airways to the Directorate of Civil Aviation of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The money is for navigation and other services.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also revised the existing route schedules and
put both parties' frequencies to three flights per week.
</P>
<P>
The routes to be operated by Nigeria Airways are
Lagos-Douala-Entebbe-Nairobi-Bombay.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Airways will fly Nairobi-Entebbe-Kinshasa-Lagos-Accra.
</P>
<P>
Their talks also covered aviation security, designation of
airlines, code-sharing and other problems.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria Airways stopped flight operations to Kenya in 1992 due
to cash flow problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
