While dwelling on the 1997/98 estimates in the National
Assembly Friday, Mary Nagu said that such a move will enable more
women to take part in decision-making organs, according to a
report from the parliament.
</P>
<P>
She said that her ministry has prepared a list of women and
their academic qualifications, which might be used in considering
promotion for them to various leading positions.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Tanzanian government has made efforts to
create favorable environment for women to take part in national
development.
</P>
<P>
Mary Nagu paid tribute to the government, particularly to
President Benjamin Mkapa for the commitment to build gender
balance in this east African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
