<HEADLINE> China Controlling Township Enterprise Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- China has shut down 74,000 small
plants with serious pollution problems, or 86 percent of the total
number of plants follows a State Council decree of last year
requiring 15 types of small plants to shut down.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang Yuqing, deputy-director of the National
Environmental Protection Agency, these plants, mainly in rural
areas, range from paper mills, leather tanning factories, printing
and dyeing mills and coking plants using outdated equipment.
</P>
<P>
There are 18 province-level areas, including Beijing, Shanghai
and Tianjin, which have shut down all the polluters on their lists.
</P>
<P>
The country has had two nationwide inspections of township
enterprises with serious pollution problems in the past few years,
Wang said. 
</P>
