<HEADLINE> Foreign Financial Institutions Doing Fine in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-backed financial
institutions in Shanghai, China's leading economic center,
especially those handling Renminbi (RMB) business, have been
operating with success, according to the People's Bank of China
Shanghai Branch.
</P>
<P>
The city had 44 foreign-backed financial institutions in
business by the end of last June. Their combined capital has
increased by 16.44 percent during the first half of the year over
the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Their outstanding loans and deposits during the same period
have risen by 26.63 percent and 28.57 percent respectively. Most
of the loans have been issued to enterprises in the city.
</P>
<P>
Since last March, the Shanghai branches of six foreign-financed
banks including the Citibank of North America and the Sanwa Bank
Limited have been operating smoothly with their RMB business.
</P>
<P>
Bt the end of last June, the six banks' outstanding deposits
and loans in RMB came to 215 million yuan and 103 million yuan
respectively.  
</P>
