<HEADLINE> Accused Murderer of Late President to be Extradited </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Retired army officer Bazlul Huda,
one of the absconding accused in the Bangabandhu murder case, will
be extradited back from Thailand for trial, said official sources.
</P>
<P>
Major (Retd) Huda, who allegedly fired on late president
Bangabandhu in a coup in 1975, was earlier arrested in Bangkok as
he committed stealing at a department store there.
</P>
<P>
In the bloody coup on August 15, 1975, the then president
Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman and most of his family members
were killed by a group of military officers.
</P>
<P>
According to a prosecution witness in the on-going trial of
Bangabandhu Murder Case, the then Major Noor and Captain Bazlul
Huda shot dead Bangabandhu, father of the incumbent Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina.
</P>
<P>
During the trial proceedings on July 28, the witness, Mohammad
Quddus Skder, said he was standing behind Major Noor and Captain
Huda when they gunned down the father of the nation.
</P>
<P>
The extradition of Huda becomes possible following the cabinet
at a meeting on Thursday approved Extradition Treaty 1997 between
Bangladesh and Thailand, said the official sources.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that the government was also trying to bring
back other fugitives, now staying in different countries of the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
