<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Olympic Committee Renamed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Olympic organization of
Hong Kong has renamed itself as the Amateur Sports Federation and
Olympic Committee of Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
This move, approved at the organization's extraordinary council
meeting here Friday night, is a ratification of an agreement
reached in Hong Kong on July 3 this year between the International
Olympic Committee and the HKASF&AMP;OC.
</P>
<P>
The agreement requires the local Olympic committee to be
identified in the designation as "Hong Kong, China" and its emblem
to feature the change accordingly.
</P>
<P>
A design presented by HKASF&AMP;OC emblem in March this year
caused criticism from local sports community and was not ratified
by the IOC, the world governing body of sports.
</P>
<P>
HKASF&AMP;OC sent a new emblem design last month which was done
according to the terms set in the July 3 agreement and had it
approved by Juan Antonio Samaranch, IOC's president.
</P>
<P>
The new emblem features the flower Bauhinia, which is adopted
in the emblem of the Hong Kong Special Administration Region, with
the Olympic Five Rings and the Chinese characters "Hong Kong,
China" all within a circle followed by English characters "Hong
Kong" with "China" underneath. 
</P>
</TEXT>
