<HEADLINE> More Ricefields to Be Affected by Drought in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The acreage of Indonesian
ricefields affected by drought is expected to reach some
250,000-300,000 hectares up to the end of this year, Agriculture
Minister Sjarifudin Baharsjah said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The affected areas would not be in as serious conditions as in
1994 when a drought lasted longer and brought a drier season,
Antara news agency today quoted the minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the acreage of ricefields totally damaged was
also smaller than that in 1994 but he made no prediction for this
year.
</P>
<P>
He remained the public about an earlier announcement that up to
the second week of July 1997, the current drought had affected
112,889 hectares of ricefields, of which 5,870 hectares were
totally damaged.
</P>
<P>
The minister also referred to preparations being made in the
face of the raining season later this year.
</P>
<P>
Based on a meteorological and geophysics agency forecast, the
current drought would at least last until next September or
October, he said. 
