<HEADLINE> Airport Explosion Injuries 4 Officers in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Four officers of Bangladesh's Air
Force suffered serious burn injuries as a gas cylinder exploded
Thursday during a repair work of the side-barrier of the airport
runway in southern Cox's Bazar district, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The injured officers were rushed to a local hospital and later
shifted to a military hospital in the capital Dhaka by a
helicopter.
</P>
<P>
Airport sources said a fire broke out at the work site in the
south portion of the runway as the gas cylinder exploded with a
big bang Thursday noon, leaving the four seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, a Bangladesh Biman flight took the runway for
Dhaka just 10 minutes before the explosion, the sources added.
</P>
