<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: ASEAN Starts Celebrating 30th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) today started a year-long celebration of its
30th anniversary with a flag-hoisting ceremony and the release of
30 white doves at the ASEAN Secretariat building here.
</P>
<P>
In an apparent attempt to show the power of the regional
grouping, the marching band chosen to entertain the guests at the
ceremony is called the Bulldozer, which played the ASEAN theme
song and other music.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony, which was attended by ambassadors and
diplomats from the nine members of the grouping, ASEAN Secretary
General Ajit Singh said the ASEAN has virtually realized the
vision of its founding fathers to establish a regional community
of all the 10 states in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
By realizing the 10-state ASEAN vision, the ASEAN would "bind
themselves together in friendship and cooperation and, through
joint efforts and sacrifices, secure for their peoples and for
posterity the blessings of peace, freedom and prosperity," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Laos and Myanmar joined the ASEAN last month and the entry of
Cambodia is merely a matter of time, he added.
</P>
<P>
Singh praised the achievements made by the ASEAN since its
formation 30 years ago, saying the ASEAN has become the fourth
largest trading entity in the world as well as the most dynamic
with a gross domestic product that boasts an average growth rate
of 7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Singh pointed out that the ASEAN is standing at a crossroads --
that of the conclusion of one generation and the commencement of
another. "Of the days to come, one thing is certain -- the
challenges before us are immeasurable," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"Tomorrow belongs to today's children," he declared.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN was established on August 8, 1967, in Bangkok,
Thailand, with the signing of the Bangkok Declaration by the five
original member countries, namely Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Brunei Darussalam joined the grouping in 1984 while Vietnam
became the seventh member in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN admitted Laos and Myanmar as full members at a
ceremony held in Petaling Jaya, Malaysia, on July 23 this year.
</P>
<P>
The accession of Cambodia, which was supposed to join the ASEAN
simultaneously with Laos and Myanmar, was postponed due to
problems in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the ASEAN Secretariat, besides activities arranged
by the secretariat, regional and country activities will be
organized to celebrate the ASEAN's birthday. ASEAN missions in
other countries as well as dialogue partner countries will also
hold a series of commemorative activities.
</P>
<P>
Official celebrations will be kicked off in earnest tonight
when Indonesian President Soeharto hosts a lavish reception here.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the year-long celebrations is expected to be
the commemorative ASEAN informal summit to be held in Kuala Lumpur
from December 14 to 16, 1997, and attended by the ASEAN heads of
state and government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
