<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparatory Meeting of Korean Talks Adjourned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials from China, the
United States, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
and South Korea ended here today their first session of the
preparatory meeting for the four-party talks on a peace mechanism
on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The second session is scheduled to be held in New York in
mid-September.
</P>
<P>
During the session which began on Tuesday in Columbia
University in New York City, the four delegations explained their
principal stand towards the establishment of the peace mechanism
and the proposed four-party talks.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed procedural issues concerning the four-party
talks, including the date, participating levels, venue and agenda,
sources close to the session told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Agreements were reached on the date, participating levels and
venue although there are still some differences on the agenda of
the conference, according to the same sources.
</P>
<P>
The four delegations agreed to begin their conference in Geneva
six weeks after they finalize all details, including an agenda.
Delegations will be led by high-level officials authorized by the
foreign ministers of the four countries, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
In his keynote speech at the session, Chen jian, Assistant
Chinese Foreign Minister and head of the Chinese delegation,
stressed that China is positive about the establishment of a peace
mechanism on the Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
China has all along maintained that given the changes in the
inaternational situation, it is a practical and feasible approach
to replace the existing armistice mechanism with a peace
mechanism, for it helps to improve relations among the parties
concerned and achieve long-term peace and stability, and serves
the interests of all the parties, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the four-party conference, China will adhere to its
persistent stance of safeguarding peace and stability of the
Peninsula, support North-South reconciliation and improvement of
relations between the DPRK and the United States, Chen added.
</P>
<P>
He also said that it is China's sincere hope that a peace
mechanism will be established as soon as possible through frank
and sincere consultations among the parties concerned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
