<HEADLINE> Ukraine Embarks on Agricultural Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian agricultural reform is
underway to bring about more functional management, a senior
Ukrainian official told a news briefing today.
</P>
<P>
Yuri Karasyk, minister of the Ukrainian Agro-Industrial
Complex, said his ministry planned to introduce new economic
mechanisms to boost agricultural modernization. The granting of
long-term loans to farmers could be a concrete step.
</P>
<P>
Another important measure was the establishment of an Equipment
Lease Fund to develop agricultural engineering, said Karasyk.
</P>
<P>
The Fund would be set up with money from the state and
interested people. The money previously allocated for grain
purchases would also go to the Fund.
</P>
<P>
Sergi Ryzguk, deputy minister of the Agro-industrial Complex,
disclosed that the state has decided to cancel its contracts for
grain, sugar and sunflower seeds next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
