<HEADLINE> Indian Government Again Suffers Setback in House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The United Front government was
severely embarrassed in the Rajya Sabha (the upper house of
parliament) on Thursday when the opposition Bharatiya Janata party
(BJP) forced the defeat of a bill sponsored by the government, the
Indian Express said today.
</P>
<P>
The bill was brought about to amend the country's presidential
and vice-presidential elections act adopted in 1952.
</P>
<P>
This was the second setback that the government suffered in the
past two days.
</P>
<P>
The 13-party United Front government on Wednesday suffered a
major embarrassment when it was forced to withdraw a controversial
bill on insurance reform in the Lok Sabha (the lower house of
parliament).
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral went to the Rajya Sabha on
Thursday evening to plead with the BJP to pass the ordinance
designed to amend the presidential and vice- presidential
elections act but the BJP refused to accede to his request.
</P>
<P>
The BJP, instead, pressed for a voting on a statutory
resolution moved by the party earlier in the day disapproving the
bill introduced by the government.
</P>
<P>
The government was hopeless outnumbered because many members of
the Congress Party which supports the government from outside have
gone to Calcutta, West Bengal, to attend a crucial plenary of the
party on August 8-10.
</P>
<P>
The BJP resolution disapproving the government-sponsored bill
was passed in a voice vote without a division.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
