<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal, Austria Sign Air Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Nepal and Austria have signed
an air service agreement which will allow two or more airlines to
operate seven flights a week between the two countries, local
newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed in Vienna, capital of Austria, any
type of aircraft and private airlines will be permitted to serve
the Nepal-Austria route.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian Airline is expected to start the Kathmandu-Vienna
flight early next year.
</P>
<P>
But the agreement does not provide Austria with the rights over
India and Thailand points.
</P>
<P>
So far Nepal has signed bilateral air service agreements with
23 countries including Austria, the reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
