<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Election of New PM, Cambodia's Internal Affairs, says Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas said Thursday that Ung Huot's election as Cambodia's first
prime minister is the country's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Attending an Association of Southeast Asian Nations ceremony
here last night, Alatas said the recognition or non-recognition of
Ung Huot as Cambodia's first prime minister is nothing to
Indonesia, because Indonesia's recognition applies to the state,
not the government of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Cambodian's National Assembly on Wednesday approved the
nomination of Foreign Minister Ung Huot as the country's new first
prime minister in place of Prince Norodom Ranariddh.
</P>
<P>
Asked about ASEAN's attitude to Ung Huot's election, Alatas
said: "We must wait until a ministerial meeting convenes in
Singapore next Monday."
</P>
<P>
Cambodia was scheduled to join ASEAN last month, but was barred
from entry following the political crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN, which now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam, is
making efforts to find a solution to Cambodia's political crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
