<HEADLINE> Chile's Foreign Debt Tops 24 Billion Dollars by June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Chile's foreign debt amounted to
24.432 billion U.S. dollars in June, a rise of 1.453 billion
dollars over last year's 22.979 billion dollars, the country's
Central Bank said today.
</P>
<P>
About 5.399 billion dollars of the total came from the public
sector, while the remaining 19.033 billion dollars were incurred
by the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The bank also said that the country's trade surplus amounted to
529.5 billion dollars in July, although a trade deficit is
foreseen for the second half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The country's foreign exchange reserve totaled 17.488 billion
dollars in July, 2.014 billion dollars more than the 15.474
billion dollars at the end of 1996, the bank said. 
</P>
