<HEADLINE> Brazil's Vehicle Sales Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- About 989,000
domestically-made motor vehicles were sold in Brazil in the first
seven months this year, an increase of 18.4 percent over the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
In July, 144,000 locally-made vehicles were sold, a 5.7 percent
drop in comparison with June, the National Association of Motor
Vehicles Manufacturers said today.
</P>
<P>
If imported vehicles were included, the July sales rose to
171,000 units, a 4.59 percent growth over the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's vehicle production in the seven-month period this year
reached a record high of 1.2 million units.
</P>
<P>
The country exported during the same period 207,000 vehicles,
30.5 percent more than in the same time in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's vehicle production will reach 2 million units this
year, ranking the country seventh in the world. 
</P>
