<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Approves New Traffic Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Metro Manila mayors and bus
operators have approved two new traffic schemes proposed by the
Metropolitan Manila Development Authority (MMDA), local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under the Vehicle Occupancy Optimization Scheme, private
vehicles with less than three passengers will be restricted from
some major thoroughfares between 9 a.m. and 4 p.m.
</P>
<P>
Exempted from the new rules are motorcycles, commercial
delivery vehicles, public utility vehicles and vehicles carrying
handicapped persons, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The other plan, the Seven Bus Stops Color Coding Scheme, will
limit public utility buses to a certain number of stops along
EDSA, a main street in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Both schemes were planned to replace the current odd-even car
plate program that has failed to reduce traffic jams in the city.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
