<HEADLINE> Sweden to Aid Polish Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Swedish Prime Minister Goran
Persson ended his one-day working visit to Poland here today,
promising to provide Poland with 125 million Swedish krona
(about 54 million U.S. dollars) for flood relief work.
</P>
<P>
Persson, who made the special trip here to examine
flood-stricken Silesia, in southwest Poland, said the money would
be applied mainly to environmental protection, housing and water
and drainage systems in the affected regions.
</P>
<P>
The floods, the worst in more than 200 years in Central Europe,
caused severe damage in Germany, Poland, and in the Czech and
Slovak republics.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that over 100 people died in the floods in
Poland and the Czech Republic in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
Polish Prime Minister Wlodzimierz Cimoszewicz today accompanied
Persson to inspect the disaster area. 
</P>
