<HEADLINE> Regional Conference on AIDS Starts in Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A regional conference on AIDS
opened here today for discussions of ways to combat the deadly
scourge.
</P>
<P>
The Latin American and the Caribbean forum stressed the urgency
of cooperation in the fight against AIDS, amid the dramatic
advance of the pandemic.
</P>
<P>
The conference, which will end on August 13, is attended by
experts and leaders from international and non-government
organizations, as well as many people who have been infected with
the human immuno-deficiency virus (HIV).
</P>
<P>
An exhibition is being held in Havana depicting the efforts of
Cuban scientific institutions in the search for a vaccine to
counter the epidemic.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations says more than eight million people across
the world have been affected by the syndrome, and nearly six
million have died of AIDS. 
</P>
