<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Consumer Debt Unchanged in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The consumer credit in the
U.S. remained unchanged in June, the first time in four years, the
U.S. Federal Reserve (Fed) reported today.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Fed said that consumer debt outstanding was unchanged
at a seasonally adjusted 1.22 trillion dollars following increases
at annual rates of 2.5 percent in May and 8.9 percent in April.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that the consumer debt outstanding in the
country hasn't grown since May 1993.
</P>
<P>
The report said that credit-card debt in June grew at an annual
rate of 5.8 percent, compared with rates of 4.1 percent in May and
6.8 percent in April.
</P>
<P>
Auto loans outstanding fell at an annual rate of 0.2 percent
following gains at rates of 0.4 percent in May and 11.7 in April.
</P>
<P>
Other kinds of consumer debt, which includes loans for mobile
homes, education, boats and vacations, shrank at a 9.5 percent
annual rate, the steepest decline since December. The decline
followed increases at a 2.5 percent rate in May and an 8.8 percent
rate in April.
</P>
<P>
The report doesn't include home mortgages or home equity loans.
</P>
<P>
The report fits with other economic data showing U.S. consumers
took a rest during the second quarter after a spending spree
during the first quarter of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970808.0282 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign-backed Firms Contributing to East China Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The port city of Weihai, in
Shandong Province on China's east coast, no longer depends solely
on foreign trade companies to export goods.
</P>
<P>
The city's overseas-financed firms exported 750 million US
dollars worth of goods in the first half of the year, accounting
for nearly 65 percent of the city's total exports for the period.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, foreign trade companies exported only 230 million
dollars worth goods during the same period, accounting for only
20.3 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Less than a decade ago, the city was still counting on its
foreign trade companies for all its exports.
</P>
<P>
A number of enterprises with export licenses are now playing an
increasingly important role in the city's foreign trade, and
exports of 16 enterprises exceed 10 million dollars each.
</P>
<P>
The city has trade relations with 83 countries and regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
