<HEADLINE> Henan Law on Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Provincial People's Congress of Henan, central China, recently
passed a local law titled "Regulations on the Supervision of
Commodities Trading in Henan Province".
</P>
<P>
The goal of the law, which went into effect on July 1, is to
standardize activities in local markets and protect the rights
of market owners, managers and consumers.
</P>
<P>
Henan had established 5,540 markets by the end of 1996, with
the total sales volume of 77.1 billion yuan.  
</P>
