<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Grain Prices Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhengzhou, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Prices on the Zhengzhou
wholesale market, one of the country's major grain markets, edged
up during July following a central government decision to purchase
grain at protected prices.
</P>
<P>
Grain prices for late July averaged 1.28 yuan/kg., up 18.5
percent on June levels, with prices for wheat futures also on the
rise.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts attributed rising prices to the implementation
of the State Council circular calling for open-ended grain
purchases at protected prices.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in Henan, one of the country's major grain production
bases, harvested over 23.89 billion kg. of summer grain, up 3.4
billion kg. on the previous year's harvest.
</P>
<P>
However, the record harvest sparked falling prices, with the
lowest price for wheat hitting 0.98 yuan/kg..
</P>
<P>
Farmers are delighted that rising wheat prices have been
accompanied by rising prices for rice and corn.
</P>
<P>
As of August 5, the province had doubled last year's figures by
purchasing 3.2 billion kg. of grain beyond state quotas at
protected prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
