<HEADLINE> Four-Party Preparatory Meeting to Continue in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials from the United
States, China, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and South
Korea today failed to reach an agreement on an agenda for the
four-party talks on Korean Peninsula peace, local news reports
quoted American officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that negotiators from the four countries would
meet again in September in New York to complete work on preparing
details and logistics for the peace talks proposed by Washington
and Seoul in April 1996.
</P>
<P>
The four delegations began the preparatory meeting Tuesday in
Columbia University in New York City with an aim to set the date,
venue and agenda of the four-party talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
