offer to 9500 public transport workers.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- The continuing jobs crisis revealed yesterday in Australian
Bureau of Statistics figures for July, which showed an increase
from 8.5 to 8.7 percent, will be a key agenda item at a special
two-day cabinet meeting to be chaired by Prime Minister John
Howard starting in Monday.  
