<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Denounces Turkey, Turkish Cypriots Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The United States today
criticized Turkey and Turkish Cypriots in northern Cyprus for
their agreement on partial integration.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and the Turkish Cypriots signed the agreement Wednesday
to establish a committee on coordinating better relations.
</P>
<P>
"We do not think this announcement was helpful and we don't
want to see any steps taken which undermine the U.N. negotiation
process or which move toward the permanent partition of the
island," State Department spokesman James Rubin told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriots established a republic in 1983, but was
recognized only by Turkey.
</P>
<P>
It was said that the Turkish Cypriots reached the agreement
with Turkey in an attempt to counter the European Union's decision
to start membership talks with the Greek Cypriots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
