<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia, Portugal End Talks on East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia and Portugal
today ended their four-day talks on the question of East Timor,
said a statement by the spokesman's office.
</P>
<P>
This was in line with the agreement reached at the ninth round
of talks held by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan with the
foreign ministers of the two countries on June 19-20, 1997, said
the statement.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the senior officials were held in a constructive
and business-like atmosphere. The delegations of the two
governments would return to their capitals and had agreed to
resume the talks at a later date, added the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
